  "doc_id": "60675",
  "text": "More recently, [CITATION_1] proposed graph attention networks (GATs) to summarize neighborhood states by using masked selfattentional layers [CITATION_2] . Compared to our work, their motivations and network structures are different. In particular, each node only attends to its neighbors in GATs whereas AG-GCNs measure the relatedness among all nodes. The network topology in GATs remains the same, while fully connected graphs will be built in AG-GCNs to capture long-range semantic interactions.",
